@Injections.Citation: "In case 1 (Fig. 1), the bulk of the injection site was located in the medial portion of PM although PI and PL were affected. However, in addition, the injection site affected nucleus limitans and a region termed the densocellar portion of the medial dorsal nucleus (MD) by Olszewski ('52) which has also been classified as part of the pulvinar (Aronson and Papez, '34; Crouch, '34)."

@LabelledSites_Descriptions.Citation:
"The cortical areas involved were 8A, 45 and 46 on the convexity and areas 11 and 12 on the orbital surface of the hemisphere...
In both cases [cases 1 and 2] there was no evidence for projections to the medial aspect of prefrontal granular cortex."

@Injections.Citation: "In case 19 (fig. 7), the injection site involved mainly the dorsolateral parts of PM although the lateral posterior nucleus and MD was affected by the periphery of the injection site."

@LabelledSites_Descriptions.Citation: "Areas 21 and 22 within the superior temporal sulcus were involved as was the more caudal parts of the insular cortex."

@Injections.Citation: "In case 2 (fig. 2) , the injection site was somewhat smaller. It involved primarily the medial part of PM, however, as in case 1, nucleus limitans and the densocellular portion of MD were slightly affected by the periphery of the injection site."

@LabelledSites_Descriptions.Citation: "The distribution of the efferents from this region closely paralleled those seen in case 1. In both cases there was no evidence for projections to the medial aspect of prefrontal granular cortex."

@Injections.Citation: "In case 3L, the injection site involved the caudal part of PI as well as the caudal and lateral parts of PL (fig. 9)."

@LabelledSites_Descriptions.Citation: "Heavy silver deposits were restricted to the occipital lobe and especially cortex within the inferior occipital sulcus involving areas 19 and 18 primarily in the depth of this sulcus."

@Injections.Citation: "In case 3R (fig. 10), the injection site involved the dorsolateral parts of PL ..."
@Injections.Comments: The injection shown in FIgure 10 involves TJ76-R as well as the surrounding white matter.

@LabelledSites_Descriptions.Citation: "... occipital lobe projections from neurons located in this region were to 19 within the caudal part of the superior temporal sulcus, to 18 on the medial surface above the calcarine sulcus and within and above the medial parietooccipital fissure and to both 19 and 18 within the caudal extent of the intraparietal sulcus."

@Injections.Citation: "In case 4, the injection site mainly involved the rostral levels of PI but also affected the caudal parts of the lateral geniculate nucleus (LG)."
@Injections.Comments: This injection also involves the white matter between LG and the reticular nucleus.

@LabelledSites_Descriptions.Citation:
"Above background levels of silver grains were observed over the entire length of lunate sulcus involving areas 19 and 18... 
In addition, deposits of silver grains were observed over area 17, the primary visual cortex."

@Injections.Citation: "In case 5 (fig. 6), the injection site involved mainly the most lasteral parts of PM and the medial parts of PL to a lesser extent."

@LabelledSites_Descriptions.Citation: "Efferents to temporal lobe from this injection site distributed to the more caudal and ventral parts of temporal lobe than those neurons involved in cases 1 and 2. The areas involved were areas 20, 21 and 22..."

@Injections.Citation: "The injection site in te left thalmamus of animal 8 (case 8L in fig. 11) mainly involved the lateral parts of the PL although PI and oral pulvinar (PO) were slightly affected by the periphery of the injection site."
"In case 6, the injection site as indicated in figure 5 was restricted to the orbital surface ... and covered areas 10,  11, 12, 13 and 14."

@LabelledSites_Descriptions.Citation: "In this instance also, HRP labeled neurons in pulvinar were confined to PM, especially  the medial part of PM... posetively labeled neurons were also noted in nucleus limitans, the suprageniculate nucleus and the densocellular portion of MD."

@Injections.Citation: "In case 7 (fig. 3), the injection site ... involving cortex within the concavity of arcuate sulcus, i.e., areas 8A, 45 and 46."

@LabelledSites_Descriptions.Citation: "In pulvinar, the HRP labeled neurons were restricted to PM (figs. 3, 4) with the greatest concentration of the cells being found in the medial part of PM. In addition, however, posetively labeled cells were also noted in the densocellular part of MD (figs 3, 4), and in nucleus limitans as well as in the suprageniculate nucleus."

publication.title: Areal and laminar distribution of some pulvinar cortical efferents in rhesus monkey
